@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About - Trucks Weighing Web App";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="h4 mb-3">About</h1>
    <hr />

    <p>
        This web application is designed for ship officers and marine surveyors to perform accurate draught survey calculations.
    </p>

    <p>
        It allows you to keep your data securely in the database and perform surveys across multiple devices.
    </p>


    <h2 class="h4 mt-4">Features</h2>
    <hr />


    <p>The app simplifies the draught survey process, and ensures reliable and consistent reporting.</p>
    <p>Keep your data securely in the database and perform surveys across multiple devices under your account.</p>
    <p>Create, edit, delete, and store your inspections.</p>
    <p>Keep in database main vessel information (LBP, Light Ship, distances draught marks from PP, etc.), and automatically reuse it for the future inpections.</p>
    <p>Autofill the hydrostatic data based on previous inspections or saved enties.</p>
    <p>Keep all vessel and inspection data private and accessible only to the user who created it.</p>
    <p>Add and update your notes during measurements.</p>
    <p>Export results to Excel for reporting, printing, or further editing, using ready-to-use public templates.</p>
    <p>Request a custom Excel template with your company details and header, accessible only in your account.</p>

    <hr />
    <p class="small text-muted mt-4">
        See also our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
    
</div>

